snippet.textDisplay: The people who demonstrated in support of Djokovic in Australia only made it worse for him. They tipped it over the line for the Australian  authorities to use 'good order' reasons to deport him from the country, because public sentiments against  Djokovic solidified after those little episodes. It may have felt better for them to behave badly, some also say in an over-the-top, nationalistic and fanatical manner, but it worked against Djokovic and he himself was more than likely hoping they kept quiet as he knew it wasn't helping his cause. Hope there's a lesson in that for some people.
